message.text:
☆* ゜ﾟ*☆祝・50,000いいね！Reached over 50,000 likes!☆*゜ﾟ*☆

Thank you to all our friends for liking our page! Stay tuned for more Japan Foundation Updates;)))
いつも国際交流基金を応援してくださり、ありがとうございます！これからもよろしくお願いします！！！

Here is our thank you gift from The Japan Foundation headquarters staff. 
This movie is so-called "Pika Pika Douga（ピカピカ動画）". It is a home-made short movie which became very popular here in Japan especially for shooting a message video to celebrate a friend's wedding. 
Search "Pika Pika Douga" online and discover many creative movies! That's what you call artistic craftsmanship! Can you guess how it is taken?

message.text:
It is TANABATA（七夕、たなばた）, a Star Festival today! 
What would you wish upon a star?

Casula (Australia): July 9-12 Tanabata Art & Storytelling Workshop
キャスラ（オーストラリア）：7月9日～12日　七夕ワークショップ「星に願いを」 
http://www.jpf.org.au/jpfevents/14-tanabata/

Tanabata, literally meaning "Evening of the seventh", celebrates the tale of star lovers Orihime（織姫）, the star of Vega, and Hikoboshi（彦星）, the star of Altair, who became separated by the Milky Way（天の川、あまのがわ） and can only meet once a year on 7 July. In Japan, people write wishes on colorful strips of paper called "Tanzaku（短冊）" and hang it on a bamboo tree with decorations for Tanabata Festival.

Some say they can't meet on a rainy day like today in Tokyo. Others say it rains because of their tears from joy. Hope they cry with joy today and your wishes come true!

本日は七夕！日本では短冊に願い事を紙に書いて、笹に飾ります。今日の東京のように雨の日には2人は会えないという人もいるけど...うれし泣きで雨が降るといういい伝えも！？織姫と彦星が会えて、みんなの願いが叶いますように。

message.text:
Spain: Madrid-July 4 / Barcelona-July 5 Demonstration of Japanese Sword Engraving 
スペイン：マドリード(7/4)、バルセロナ(7/5)、日本刀レクチャー＆銘切りデモンストレーション

"Evangelion and Japanese Sword" Exhibition will be in Spain TOMORROW! 　Be the witness to this amazing craftsmanship! 

On the blades of the Japanese swords, you can often find a beautiful signature of the swordsmith called "銘(Mei)." A Mei is a "cut" by the swordsmith with a chisel and a hammer. We use the expression "cut" instead of "engrave" because the swordsmith "cuts" open the hard surface of the blade by using simple gears. Mr. Akihira Kawasaki, a swordsmith, will show this incredible skill live. 

「ヱヴァンゲリヲンと日本刀展」が明日からスペインで開催！これにあわせ、刀鍛冶職人・川崎晶平氏によるデモンストレーションを本日と明日実施！美技を目撃せよ！
